{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "0f996980-7bb7-4da2-b4df-bf8847ad1f80",
    "name": "WhatNext Voice Microservice",
    "description": "Postman collection for testing the Node.js Voice Assistant microservice. Auth token must come from the existing .NET backend.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "voice_base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8980"
    },
    {
      "key": "dotnet_access_token",
      "value": "PASTE_DOTNET_JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{voice_base_url}}/health",
              "host": [
                "{{voice_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Checks if the voice microservice is running."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('service is voice-assistant-service', function () {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.service).to.eql('voice-assistant-service');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 Auth Proxy",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Current User From .NET Token",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{dotnet_access_token}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{voice_base_url}}/api/voice/me",
              "host": [
                "{{voice_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "voice",
                "me"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Validates the .NET JWT token through this voice service. If JWT_SHARED_SECRET is configured, token is verified locally. Otherwise the service calls DOTNET_AUTH_ME_PATH on the .NET backend."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 .NET Action Proxy Smoke Tests",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Test Task Through .NET Backend",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{dotnet_access_token}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Voice microservice test task\",\n  \"description\": \"Created from Postman through Node voice microservice\",\n  \"priority\": \"medium\",\n  \"status\": \"todo\",\n  \"dueDate\": \"2026-06-13T10:00:00.000Z\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{voice_base_url}}/api/voice/test-task",
              "host": [
                "{{voice_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "voice",
                "test-task"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Smoke test that forwards a task create request to your existing .NET backend using the bearer token."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('task create forwarded successfully', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 Socket.IO Manual Test Instructions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Socket.IO Test Guide",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{voice_base_url}}/health",
              "host": [
                "{{voice_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Postman collections do not reliably export Socket.IO requests in collection v2.1 format. Create a new Socket.IO request manually in Postman:\n\n1. New > Socket.IO.\n2. URL: {{voice_base_url}}\n3. Auth payload:\n{\n  \"token\": \"{{dotnet_access_token}}\"\n}\n4. Connect.\n5. Add listeners:\n   - voice:pong\n   - voice:ready\n   - voice:warning\n   - voice:error\n   - transcript:partial\n   - transcript:final\n   - assistant:text\n   - assistant:audio\n   - voice:closed\n6. Emit event: voice:ping with body {}\n   Expected: voice:pong\n7. Emit event: voice:start with body {}\n   Expected: voice:ready\n8. Emit event: voice:stop with body {}\n   Expected: voice:closed\n\nFor real audio, emit binary linear16 PCM 16k mono chunks to voice:audio, then emit voice:commit."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
